Title : David Scearce
Text : '''David Scearce''' is a lawyer and screenwriter.

==Career==

===Law===
Scearce earned a business degree from [[Wilfrid Laurier University]] and a law degree from the [[University of British Columbia]] before joining the [[Department of Justice (Canada)|Justice Department]].<ref name=clerk>{{cite web|url=http://www.clerk.gc.ca/eng/prsns.asp?featureID=0&pageID=196&prsnID=36&thmID=0&dptmntID=0|title=David Scearce|publisher=[[Clerk of the Privy Council (Canada)|Clerk of the Privy Council]]|date=27 September 2012|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref>

===Film===
In 2000, Scearce decided to write screenplays in his spare time.<ref name=clerk/><ref name=globe>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/david-scearce-white-collar-by-day-red-carpet-by-night/article4188558/|title= David Scearce: White collar by day, red carpet by night |date=4 December 2009|work=[[The Globe and Mail]] |first=Marsha|last=Lederman|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> One of his first attempts was an adaptation of a favourite novelâ€”''A Single Man'' by [[Christopher Isherwood]].  [[Don Bachardy]], Isherwood's surviving partner who managed the rights to the story, approved of the script and it was then picked up by fashion designer and first-time film director [[Tom Ford]]. ''[[A Single Man]]'', starring [[Colin Firth]] and [[Julianne Moore]], premiered at the [[Venice Film Festival]] in September 2009 and was released in December 2009.<ref name=straight>{{cite web|url=https://www.straight.com/movies/vancouverite-david-scearce-succeeds-single-man-screenplay |date=22 December 2009 |work=[[The Georgia Straight]] |title=Vancouverite David Scearce succeeds with A Single Man screenplay |first=Ken |last=Eisner |accessdate=29 April 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429205201/http://www.straight.com/movies/vancouverite-david-scearce-succeeds-single-man-screenplay |archivedate=29 April 2014 |df= }}</ref>  It and its cast and crew received critical acclaim as well as numerous awards and nominations, including a [[Critics' Choice Movie Award]] nomination for Best Screenplay and an [[Independent Spirit Award]] nomination for [[Independent Spirit Award for Best First Screenplay|Best First Screenplay]].<ref name=globe/>

Scearce's second film adaptation, ''[[Measure of a Man (film)|Measure of a Man]]'', a [[coming-of-age story]] based on [[Robert Lipsyte]]'s novel [[One Fat Summer|''One Fat Summer'']], starring [[Blake Cooper]] and [[Donald Sutherland]], was released in 2018.[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2670882/releaseinfo]

In 2018, Scearce was hired by the Michael Grandage Company to write an adaptation of ''Jack and Lem'', a biography by David Pitts about President [[John F. Kennedy]] and his gay best friend, [[Lem Billings]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/michael-grandage-to-helm-movie-adaptation-of-jack-and-lem|title=Michael Grandage to Helm Movie Adaptation of Jack and Lem|last=Clement|first=Olivia|date=25 July 2018|website=Playbill|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2019-07-21}}</ref>

